        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Jmintz\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"1690\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://sea1.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/jmintz/48/451_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Jmintz:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>CouchDB Layer for FoundationDB - this code covers the stateless layer of CouchDB that will interact with FoundationDB including, but not limited to, CRUD functionality, map indices (not Mango ones yet) and materialized views<br>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/apache/couchdb/tree/prototype/fdb-layer\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">https://github.com/apache/couchdb/tree/prototype/fdb-layer </a></p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I saw a few weeks ago that <a href=\"https://lists.apache.org/thread/9gby4nr209qc4dzf2hh6xqb0cn1439b7\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">efforts are redirected towards CouchDB 3.x</a>, I\u2019m wondering if the basecode is still accessible? The link provided above is not working anymore:</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Jmintz\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"1690\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://sea1.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/jmintz/48/451_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Jmintz:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>CouchDB Layer for FoundationDB - this code covers the stateless layer of CouchDB that will interact with FoundationDB including, but not limited to, CRUD functionality, map indices (not Mango ones yet) and materialized views<br>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/apache/couchdb/tree/prototype/fdb-layer\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">https://github.com/apache/couchdb/tree/prototype/fdb-layer </a></p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>",
